The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as object tracking and segmentation, which are typically covered under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The authors propose a new approach that involves augmenting the loss function of existing methods, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) since object tracking and segmentation are important tasks in robotics applications. Finally, the paper involves multimedia (cs.MM) since it deals with video object segmentation.
